<h2 id="IDFAQs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3 id="IDFAQSite">Using the Site</h3>
<p><strong><em>I can&rsquo;t get the site to work; what could be wrong?</em></strong><br />
This site should work with <a href="http://windows.microsoft.com/en-US/internet-explorer/downloads/ie">Internet Explorer 7 or
greater</a>,
<a href="https://www.google.com/chrome">Google Chrome</a>, or <a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new/">Mozilla Firefox</a>.
   You are also required to have the <a href="http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/">Flash Player</a> installed.</p>

<p><strong><em>The site is unresponsive or is acting strangely.  I keep clicking a button but I&rsquo;m not getting the response I expect.</em></strong>
Sometimes network performance will affect the responsiveness of the map to your changes.  In most cases, the map will catch up if just given a little time.  If not, or if you&rsquo;re unsure, you may want to log out and log back in to be sure the information you have entered has been saved properly.</p>

<p>For example:</p>

<ul>
  <li><em>In the map</em>, sometimes you may zoom quickly and the map will take a little time to refresh and have the new features come into focus. If your map doesn&rsquo;t refresh, if you see features you&rsquo;re NOT expecting, or you don&rsquo;t see features you ARE expecting, log out and log back in to resolve the issue.</li>
  <li><em>In the map</em>, you may click on the map to add a property or a meter and the pop-up dialog boxes take a long time to load.  As mentioned in the video and the quick reference, wait for the appropriate dialog to open before proceeding.  If at any time you get confused about what information has been entered, you can always exit the map and log out, then log back in and reopen the map using the &ldquo;Reporting&rdquo; button.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong><em>I forgot my password; how do I get a new one?</em></strong><br />
Go to Home page and follow the link to have it reset.  If the e-mail address associated with your account is no longer valid, then you&rsquo;ll need to <a href="&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#104;&#101;&#108;&#112;&#064;&#104;&#112;&#119;&#100;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;" title="e-mail HPWD for help">contact HPWD</a> to have your e-mail address updated in the system before you can proceed.</p>

